<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">pulling.  You have to be slick about it, there's very little range for error, but encs can chain pull singles in most of pop, ldons, tipt/vxed, KT,  WoS, MPG, and RS among other places(tho i beleive you need rs5 or to stop outside for movement buffs here).  (in places where charming's appropriate, you can charm while pulling, and while every few min this will hold a chain pull off a moment, it syncs nice with giving the group full focus on the breaking pet)
<br />
Imo the biggest thing people dont know when to do is pull with tash, and that's the biggest thing people overlook on why encs work as pullers.(well, i think knowing the right pull tool is the real trick to it, and when not to pull with tash is as important as when to pull with it, but many people overlook the benefits it gives in managing adds, and getting mobs slowed asap)
<br />

<br />
Despite the charm nerf encs are still useful for taking down named with 1-2 people in a large # of zones.  While in OOW its not worth your time to solo like we used to, or even use a pet in a group, they do alright as a tank for a moment with a bit of dps to give you time to chain nuke down a named pretty well.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
