<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Easily Speechless. The ability to drain the mobs power completely with 2 shots (about 10sec) really helps the cleric keep up on tough mobs. Really advantageous when a nice long Daunting Gaze keeps the mob out of commission while you drain its power. I foresee this being nerfed as we move forward (already has with mobs hitting harder when out of power since the Jan 4 patch) <a href="http://eqiiforums.station.sony.com/eq2/board/message?board.id=stat&message.id=44" target="_blank">http://eqiiforums.station.sony.com/eq2/board/message?board.id=stat&message.id=44</a>
<br />

<br />
I also like doing the occasional Binding Light during the fight. Not because root is of any use, but the blurred vision afterwards further reduces mobs damage output.
<br />

<br />
Stacking AE dd on pulls of 4+ mobs. If 1 or 2 adds on pulls mezz is fine, but anything more then that we can spam Storm of Lightning, Chromatic Storm, Prismatic Discord. We lose to Wizzies on AE DD, but we are more efficient then they with 1 or 2 adds by locking them down.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
